    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">To make use of the ontology in medical diagnosis, we can learn a network embedding <em>gᵢ </em>for each node <em>cᵢ </em>in the graph below — which is computed by attentions using the learned embedding <em>e</em> for node <em>i</em> and its parents. To make diagnosis predictions, like the type of disease or predicting the chance of heart failure, we multiply the ontology knowledge <em>G</em> with the current visit information <em>xt </em>and make the final prediction using a NN network. This model can be further enhanced with information on previous visits using RNN networks instead of a simple NN model.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
